在美国和[[加拿大|加拿大]]，'''乔克'''（Jock）是一种[[刻板印象|刻板印象]]，此類刻板印象經常形容[[運動員|運動員]]或是那些对[[体育|体育]]和体育文化感兴趣，而对知识文化不怎么感兴趣的人<ref>{{Cite web|title=Jock: definition of Jock in Oxford dictionary (American English) (US)|url=http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/us/definition/american_english/jock#jock-2|accessdate=8 October 2015|archive-date=2016-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160329093450/http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/us/definition/american_english/jock#jock-2}}</ref><ref name="etymonline1">{{Cite web|title=Online Etymology Dictionary on Jock|url=http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?search=jock&searchmode=none|accessdate=1 February 2011|publisher=Etymonline.com|archive-date=2017-09-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913044509/http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?search=jock&searchmode=none}}</ref>。乔克一般用于高中和大学內積極参与體育运动的學生。

在北美，与乔克意思相同的类似词還有meathead、musclebrain和musclehead<ref name="UCLA">{{Cite web|title=Jocks as a Youth Subculture|url=http://smhp.psych.ucla.edu/pdfdocs/youth/jocks.pdf|accessdate=July 16, 2016|publisher=Center for Mental Health in Schools, School Mental Health Project, Department of Psychology, UCLA, Los Angeles|archive-date=2017-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828162009/http://smhp.psych.ucla.edu/pdfdocs/youth/jocks.pdf}}</ref>。这些词則是形容运动员肌肉发达，但頭腦不是很聪明（'''四肢发达，头脑简单'''），一般人和他們只能交流與运动和锻炼有关的话题，至於其他话题則和他們無法交流。

